==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slogan
<hw>Slo"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael.
<ets>sluagh-ghairm</ets>, i.e., an army cry; <ets>sluagh</ets> army +
<ets>gairm</ets> a call, calling.]</ety> <def>The war cry, or gathering
word, of a Highland clan in Scotland.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A distinctive motto, phrase,
or cry used by any person or party to express a purpose or ideal; a
catchphrase; a rallying cry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1356 --></p>

<p><ent>sloggy</ent>⟦br⟧
